						<summary>

						<p>Uttarāpatīśvara temple, Gaṇapatīśvara shrine, west wall.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Rājakēsarivarman Year 3.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records a gift of land, to provide for two perpetual lamps for God Chirāḷadēvar in Tīruchcheṅgāṭṭukkuḍi, a <hi rend="italic">dēvadāṉam</hi> in Marukā-nāḍu by Ulakaṉ [chiṟṟa]yaṉ alias Tāppilā ••• Mūvēnda-vēḷān, a <hi rend="italic">veḷḷāḷan</hi> (a land holder) of [Iraiyā]ṉ guḍi.</p>						

						</summary>
